Image processing using Pillow¶

Import libraries¶

In [1]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from PIL import Image, ImageFilter

Read the image file¶

In [2]:
img_in = 'dog.jpg'
img = Image.open(img_in)
In [3]:
print(img.format, img.size,
      img.width, img.height, img.mode)

JPEG (1024, 768) 1024 768 RGB
In [4]:
plt.imshow(img)
plt.show()
In [5]:
img.show()
In [6]:
data=np.array(img)
print(data.shape)

(768, 1024, 3)

RGB of a pixel¶

In [10]:
print(img.getpixel((500, 70)))

(176, 150, 125)

Resize¶

In [11]:
img_small = img.resize((30,50))
plt.imshow(img_small)
plt.show()

Rotation and translation¶

In [12]:
img_rot = img.rotate(45)
plt.imshow(img_rot)
plt.show()
In [13]:
img_rot2 = img.rotate(45, expand=True)
plt.imshow(img_rot2)
plt.show()
In [14]:
img_rot_shift = img.rotate(0, translate=(200,-200))
plt.imshow(img_rot_shift)
plt.show()
In [15]:
img_rot_shift2 = img.rotate(0, translate=(200,-200),
                            fillcolor=(255,255,255))
plt.imshow(img_rot_shift2)
plt.show()

Apply filter¶

In [16]:
img_blur = img.filter(ImageFilter.GaussianBlur(radius=10))
plt.imshow(img_blur)
plt.show()

Cropping¶

In [17]:
img_crop = img.crop((300, 100, 600, 400))
plt.imshow(img_crop)
plt.show()

To gray scale¶

In [18]:
img_gray = img.convert('L')  # gray scale
plt.imshow(img_gray, cmap='gray')
plt.show()

Save to a file¶

In [19]:
img_out = 'dog_gray.jpg'
img_gray.save(img_out, quality=95)
